00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:35,120
The cough improves if you take the child
outside in the cold air.

209
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,890
Croup is quite common in the fall in,

210
00:11:38,890 --> 00:11:42,480
in contrast to many of the respiratory
viruses that peak in the winter.

211
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:44,797
There are four types of Parainfluenza, and

212
00:11:44,797 --> 00:11:47,710
type one is most often impli, implicated
with Croup.

213
00:11:47,710 --> 00:11:51,850
Parainfluenza virus buds out of the cell
only at the apical surface,

214
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:53,760
where it then infects neighboring cells.

215
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,840
This is likely why we rarely see viremia.

216
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:59,260
Because it buds out of the cell,

217
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:03,360
Parainfluenza doesn't cause cell death
like Rhinovirus, but

218
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:08,010
it does increase the replication rate of
epithelial cells so more cells are shed.

219
00:12:08,010 --> 00:12:11,529
It increases the number of mucus cells,
increasing mucus production and

220
00:12:11,529 --> 00:12:13,950
it also decreases cilary motility.

221
00:12:13,950 --> 00:12:16,510
All this together increases cellular
debris, mucous, and

222
00:12:16,510 --> 00:12:19,500
swelling all along the wall of the
trachea.

223
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,740
The subglottic area of the trachea is
already narrow in children, so

224
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:24,610
even a small amount of swelling and

225
00:12:24,610 --> 00:12:29,630
mucous will more easily cause Stenosis in
this area and cause the classic symptoms.

226
00:12:29,630 --> 00:12:30,766
Here's a picture of what the su,

