00:12:46,890 --> 00:12:51,220
Parainfluenza virus is an RNA virus like
most of the respiratory viruses.

232
00:12:51,220 --> 00:12:55,470
However, it's enveloped which is different
from some of the other RNA viruses.

233
00:12:55,470 --> 00:12:59,710
It has four serotypes and their clinical
manifestations can vary.

234
00:12:59,710 --> 00:13:00,810
Reinfections are common.

235
00:13:00,810 --> 00:13:04,280
And this could be a result of the virus
budding from the apical surface of

236
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:08,230
the cell not allowing a chance for the
immune cells to appropriately respond.

237
00:13:09,470 --> 00:13:14,700
I should point out, that Parainfluenza
virus is not related to influenza virus.

238
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:18,270
Parainfluenza virus is actually in the
family Paramyxoviridae.

239
00:13:19,490 --> 00:13:24,840
And you can see that in this family there
are two other respiratory viruses.

240
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:28,730
RSV, Respiratory Syncytial Virus and
Metapneumovirus.

